I am using slider for adjusting the distance for a camera from a node, and I noticed that for some reason the slider doesn't get focused at all.

This means that code: 

```
    // Do not move if the UI has a focused element (the console)
    if (ui->GetFocusElement())
        return;
```

cannot be used to determine if a slider is being moved/dragged.

Using the focusmode seems to fix it, but is there a reason why sliders aren't focused by default?

